## 5. Visual Encoding

### 5.1 Node Appearance

| Node Type | Border Color | Background | Badge |
|---|---|---|---|
| Blood relative | `#60a5fa` (blue) | `#eff6ff` | — |
| In-law | `#34d399` (green) | `#f0fdf4` | `IN-LAW` |
| Ex-partner | `#f87171` (red) | `#fff5f5` | `EX` |
| Deceased (any type) | `#94a3b8` (slate) | `#f1f5f9` | `✝` |

- Badge is a small pill label rendered at top-right of the node card
- Deceased overrides the type color — apply slate to any node where `deathYear` is set

### 5.2 Partner Edge Appearance

| Relationship | Stroke Color | Stroke Style | Width |
|---|---|---|---|
| `married` | `#64748b` | Solid | 2px |
| `partnered` | `#64748b` | Solid | 1.5px |
| `divorced` | `#f87171` | Dashed `6,4` | 2px |
| `separated` | `#f87171` | Dashed `3,3` | 1.5px |
| `widowed` | `#94a3b8` | Dotted `2,3` | 1.5px |

- Partner edges are **horizontal lines** drawn at mid-height of the node card
- They connect from the right edge of the left node to the left edge of the right node
- A small relationship label (e.g. `"div. 2008"`) may optionally render as centered text above the partner edge, in a 10px muted font

### 5.3 Parent Edge from Ex-Node

When a parent edge forks from a divorced couple, render the branch going to the ex-node as a **dashed line** matching the partner edge style. The branch going to the blood node remains solid.

### 5.4 Legend

Add a legend block to the SVG output, anchored to the **bottom-left** of the viewport:

- Render it as a `<g>` group with a light background rect
- It must not overlap any tree nodes — if it does, shift it to bottom-right
- Contents: one row per node type (color swatch + label) and one row per edge type (line sample + label)

---

## 6. Rendering Order (Z-Index / Paint Order)

SVG has no z-index — paint order matters. Render in this sequence:

1. Parent edges (vertical connector lines) — bottom layer
2. Partner edges (horizontal connector lines)
3. Blood nodes
4. In-law nodes
5. Ex-nodes
6. Badges and labels — top layer

---

